An Act relative to supporting primary care physicians in the commonwealth.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 29 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
2 section 2JJJJJJ the following section:-
3 2KKKKKK. (a) There shall be established and set up on the books of the commonwealth
4 a separate fund known as the Primary Care Physician Loan Repayment Fund. The fund shall be
5 credited with: (i) appropriations or other money authorized or transferred by the general court
6 and specifically designated to be credited to the fund; (ii) funds from public and private sources,
7 including, but not limited to, gifts, grants and donations; and (iii) any interest earned on the
8 assets of the fund. Amounts credited to the fund that are unexpended at the end of a fiscal year
9 shall not revert to the General Fund.
10 (b) Amounts credited to the fund may be expended, without further appropriation, by the
11 health care workforce center established in section 25L of chapter 111 for loan assistance
