12 payments under the primary care physician loan repayment program established in section 25N¼
13 of said chapter 111.
14 (c) Annually, not later than July 1, the center shall submit to the clerks of the house of
15 representatives and the senate, the house and senate committees on ways and means, the joint
16 committee on health care financing, the joint committee on mental health and substance abuse
17 and the joint committee on public health a report on the activities of the fund.
18 SECTION 2. Chapter 111 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
19 section 25N the following section:-
20 Section 25N¼. (a) There shall be a primary care physician loan repayment program
21 administered by the health care workforce center established in section 25L. The program shall
22 pay the medical school loan balance of participants who commit to practicing medicine as a
23 primary care physician in the commonwealth for at least 10 years. Each recipient shall enter into
24 a contract with the commonwealth, which shall obligate the recipient to perform a term of
25 service of not less than 10 years as a primary care physician in the commonwealth.
26 (b) The center shall promulgate regulations for the administration and enforcement of this
27 section, which shall include penalties and repayment procedures if a participant fails to comply
28 with the service contract.
29 (c) The center shall evaluate the program annually, including exit interviews of
30 participants to determine their post-program service plans and to solicit program improvement
31 recommendations.
