32 (d) Annually, not later than July 1, the center shall file a report with the governor, the
33 clerks of the house of representatives and the senate, the house and senate committees on ways
34 and means, the joint committee on health care financing, the joint committee on mental health
35 and substance abuse and the joint committee on public health. The report shall include annual
36 data and historical trends of: (i) the number of applicants, the number accepted and the number
37 of participants by race, gender, medical school, residence prior to medical school and where they
38 plan to practice after program completion; (ii) the service placement locations and length of
39 service commitments by participants; (iii) the number of participants who fail to fulfill the
40 program requirements and the reason for the failures; and (iv) program expenditures.
